header.gameNote: O'REILLY AUTO PARTS CBE CLASSIC AT EAST LANSING MI

article.headline: Louisiana-Monroe 60, N. Michigan 53
article.story: EAST LANSING, Mich. (AP) -- Lance Brasher scored 15 points to lead a balanced attack and help Louisiana-Monroe rally past Northern Michigan 60-53 Tuesday at Michigan State in the opening round of the CBE Classic. Tony Hooper had 12 points for the Warhawks (1-0), while Raphelle Turner may have saved ULM with 10 points and eight rebounds. Jerard Ajami had 27 points for NMU and was 11-for-20 from the field. Tyler Kazmierkoski added 10 for the Wildcats (0-1). The Warhawks trailed 13-4 after the first 5:39 and were down 23-20 at halftime. A 7-0 run midway through the second half gave ULN a 42-36 lead. The margin grew to 50-39 before the Wildcats rallied. But Turner's four points and three rebounds in the closing minutes kept the Warhawks ahead. ULM had a 38-29 rebound advantage and was 19-for-22 at the line, sinking 10 more free throws than NMU.
